b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](lcc17.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/1417982012/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](img/tease.jpg)  \n_The Little Clay Cart_ , by Shudraka, tr. Arthur William Ryder, [1905], at\nsacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 177\n\n### A LIST OF PASSAGES\n\n#### IN WHICH THE TRANSLATION DEPARTS FROM PARAB\'S TEXT\n\n85.15: Here _nirmit \xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5_ is apparently a mere misprint for _nirjit \xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5_.\n\n45.11: The addition of _u \xe1\xb9\xad\xe1\xb9\xadhedha tti_ seems almost necessary.\n\n53.10; 54.9; 55.11; 62.7; 66.7: In these passages I have substituted\n"shampooer" for "gambler," to prevent confusion of the shampooer with the\nunnamed gambler.\n\n57.18: I have added the stage-direction _dy \xc5\xabtakarama\xe1\xb9\x87\xe1\xb8\x8datm k\xe1\xb9\x9btv\xc4\x81_.\n\n67.5: Read _ka \xe1\xb9\x81_ for _ki \xe1\xb9\x81_.\n\n72.9: Read _ajjo bandhua \xe1\xb9\x87a\xe1\xb9\x81 samass\xc4\x81sidu\xe1\xb9\x81_ for Parab\'s _ajja bandhua \xe1\xb9\x87o\nsamassasadu_.\n\n78.5: We should probably read _b \xc4\xabhaccha\xe1\xb9\x81_ ( _b \xc4\xabbhatsam_) for _v \xc4\xabhattha\xe1\xb9\x81_.\n\n87.8: The words _cikits \xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x81 k\xe1\xb9\x9btv\xc4\x81_ seem to be part of the text, not of the\nstage-direction.\n\n97.18: I regard _nayasya_ as one word, not two ( _na yasya_ ).\n\n100.12: Read _rak \xe1\xb9\xa3\xc4\x81n_ for _rak \xe1\xb9\xa3y\xc4\x81n_.\n\n114.5: Read _\xe1\xb9\x87 aara\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81r\xc4\xab_\\- for _\xe1\xb9\x87 ara\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81r\xc4\xab_-.\n\n125.8-11: These lines I have omitted.\n\n126.4: Read _acchar \xc4\xaba_\\- ( _\xc4\x81 \xc3\xa7carya_-) for _acchar \xc4\xabdi_-.\n\n170.8: Read _eka_ \\- for _ek \xc4\x81_-.\n\n178.11: Read _va \xe1\xb8\x8d\xe1\xb8\x8dham\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87ao_ for _va \xe1\xb8\x8d\xe1\xb8\x8dham\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87aa_.\n\n184.9: Read _a_ ( _ca_ ) for _ka_.\n\n217.15: Whatever _\xc3\xa7 avo\xe1\xb8\x8dia\xe1\xb9\x81_ may be, I have translated it in accordance with\nLall\xc4\x81d\xc4\xabk\xe1\xb9\xa3ita\'s gloss, _save \xe1\xb9\xa3\xe1\xb9\xadikam_.\n\n226.2: Apparently _khala_ \\- is a misprint for _kha \xe1\xb9\x85a_-.\n\n238.10: Read - _ruciram_ for - _racitam_.\n\n259.16: Read _udv \xc4\xabk\xe1\xb9\xa3ya_ for _udv \xc4\xabjya_.\n\n262.4: Read - _bh \xc4\x81janam_ for - _bhojanam_.\n\n262.14: Read _pa \xe1\xb8\x8dicchida\xe1\xb9\x81_ ( _prat \xc4\xab\xe1\xb9\xa3\xe1\xb9\xadam_) for _pa \xe1\xb8\x8dicchidu\xe1\xb9\x81_.\n\n265.6: Read _tvay \xc4\x81_ for _may \xc4\x81_.\n\n284.14: The words _atha v \xc4\x81_ plainly belong to the text, not to the stage-\ndirection.\n\n287.2: I take _paur \xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\xa5_ as part of the stage-direction.\n\n288.8-292.9: This passage I have omitted: compare page\n[xii](lcc03.htm#page_xii).\n\n'